[74.453788, "i", "cat > FIXES_APPLIED.txt << 'EOF'\nEXPORT SCRIPT FIXES - Applied on $(date)\n\nProblem: export_users.sh was producing garbled CSV output with:\n- Emails appearing in wrong columns\n- Group memberships showing as UIDs instead of names\n- Data misalignment across fields\n\nRoot Causes Identified:\n1. BUG 1: emails.dat is tab-delimited but script used space delimiter\n2. BUG 2: Users sorted alphabetically but emails sorted by UID numerically, causing line misalignment\n3. BUG 3: groups.dat is colon-delimited but awk used default space/tab separator\n\nFixes Applied:\n1. Changed email parsing to use tab delimiter: awk -F$'\\t'\n2. Changed email lookup to use UID-based matching instead of line-based paste\n3. Added -F: flag to all awk commands parsing groups.dat\n\nResults:\n- Clean CSV output with 800 users (801 lines including header)\n- All fields in correct columns\n- Group names properly resolved from GIDs\n- Emails correctly matched to users by UID\n\nBackup: Original script saved as export_users.sh.backup\nEOF\n"]
